BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Diagnosing Asthma in Children Under Age 5
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260304T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260304T210000
DTSTAMP:20260312T061900Z
UID:b7ed467640d07286@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:OverviewPediatricians play an important role in diagnosing you
 ng patients with asthma\, but it can be difficult to make the diagnosis in
  children younger than 5 years old. In this webinar\, participants will le
 arn an approach to asthma diagnosis in this age group. Since lung testing 
 is difficult\, the diagnosis is often based on identifying signs and sympt
 oms of reversible airflow obstruction and the documentation of response to
  asthma medication. The webinar will also discuss the indications for spec
 ialized care when the diagnosis of asthma is not straightforward or respon
 se to therapy is not successful. In addition\, pediatricians will learn ab
 out practical day-to-day management issues of patients with asthma and the
  types of treatments these patients may be receiving.\n\nRegistrationRegis
 tration for all practitioners - free\n\nTo register for this activity\, pl
 ease click HERE.\n\nCreditsAMA PRA Category 1 Credits™ (1.00 hours)\, AA
 PA Category 1 CME credits (1.00 hours)\, ANCC Contact Hours (1.00 hours)\,
  Non-Physician Participation Credit (1.00 hours)\n\nTarget AudienceSpecial
 ties - Family Medicine & Community Health\, PediatricsProfessions - Advanc
 e Practice Nurse (APN)\, Fellow/Resident\, Nurse\, Physician\, Physician A
 ssociate\, Registered Nurse (RN) ObjectivesAt the conclusion of this activ
 ity\, learners should be able to:\n1. Discuss why it is often difficult to
  diagnose young children with asthma since it is a heterogeneous disorder 
 with different causes and triggers.\n2. Identify the predictors of asthma 
 and how to separate from wheezing with viral illnesses.\n3. Define the sig
 ns\, symptoms and response to therapy that may indicate asthma in young ch
 ildren.\n4. Describe when to order further testing for patients with suspe
 cted asthma.\n5. Review the indications for specialized asthma care and fu
 rther examination for asthma.\n6. Summarize the daily management of patien
 ts with asthma.\n7. Explain the treatments for asthma in children includin
 g the various medications\, environmental contro\n\nEvent URL: https://eve
 nts.stanford.edu/event/diagnosing-asthma-in-children-under-age-5\n\nSource
 : stanford_virtual
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/diagnosing-asthma-in-children-under-
 age-5
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: Diagnosing Asthma in Children Under Age 5
TRIGGER:-PT1H
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Managing Unexpected Expenses and Navigating Market Volatility
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260305T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260305T210000
DTSTAMP:20260312T061900Z
UID:6a5b8916ecb121f0@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Class/Seminar
DESCRIPTION:They say the only constant in life is change\, and the last fe
 w years have certainly brought an inordinate amount of change for all of u
 s around the world. Many people may feel unprepared to weather unexpected 
 events and expenses brought on by the pandemic\, increased cost of living\
 , or other life crisis. The volatile fluctuations in the financial markets
  add another layer of uncertainty and stress.\n\nIn this free noontime web
 inar\, you will learn important strategies you can put in place to prepare
  for unexpected expenses and navigate market volatility. You will gain a b
 etter understanding of how to assess your spending habits and discover how
  to take control of your finances with a budget\, as well as the ramificat
 ions of taking money from a workplace savings plan to get you through a di
 fficult time.\n\nWe will also explore the history of market downturns\, co
 mmon pitfalls faced by investors\, and the importance of following a plan 
 with your investments. By planning ahead and understanding all the financi
 al tools at your disposal\, you will be better equipped to weather whateve
 r comes your way.\n\nThis class will not be recorded. Attendance requireme
 nt for incentive points - at least 80% of the live session.  Request disab
 ility accommodations and access info.\n\nInstructors: Nick Maly is a Fidel
 ity Workplace Financial Consultant and has been with Fidelity since 2013. 
 He is a Certified Financial Planner professional\, investment advisor repr
 esentative\, registered securities representative\, and licensed insurance
  representative and promotes financial wellness for plan participants thro
 ugh one-on-one planning and educational events.\n\nClass details are subje
 ct to change.\n\nEvent URL: https://events.stanford.edu/event/managing-une
 xpected-expenses-and-navigating-market-volatility-2688\n\nSource: stanford
 _virtual
LOCATION:Online
URL:https://events.stanford.edu/event/managing-unexpected-expenses-and-nav
 igating-market-volatility-2688
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: Managing Unexpected Expenses and Navigating Market V
 olatility
TRIGGER:-PT1H
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
