CATEGORIES:Fred Hutch Center for AIDS Research (CFAR)
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nOnline Meeting Link: https:/
 /washington.zoom.us/meeting/register/hC13xdiQS4OKvW_Mh77qkA\nCampus room: 
 Pelton Auditorium\nAccessibility Contact: cfar@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Lectur
 es/Seminars\n\nREGISTER NOW!\n\nRegister via this link for in-person atten
 dance\nin-person registration: \nhttps://app.smartsheet.com/b/form/019ccf8
 1faa77e6d85ad09265e292660\n\nRegister via this link for virtual attendance
 \nzoom registration: \nhttps://washington.zoom.us/meeting/register/hC13xdi
 QS4OKvW_Mh77qkA\n---------------------------------------------------------
 -----------------------\n4:00pm - 5:00pm\nIN-PERSON\nCFAR Seminar Speaker:
  Gregg Gonsalves\, PhD\nTalk title: I Will Bear Witness: Policy Modeling i
 n Perilous Times\n\nGregg Gonsalves is a Professor (as of July 1) in the D
 epartment of the Epidemiology of Microbial Diseases at Yale School of Publ
 ic Health\, in the Public Health Modeling Unit and a Professor (Adjunct) a
 t Yale Law School. At Yale\, he also co-directs the Global Health Justice 
 Partnership\, an initiative of YSPH and YLS\, working at the intersections
  of health and human rights and social justice. For over 35 years\, he has
  been an AIDS activist\, working first with the AIDS Coalition to Unleash 
 Power (ACT UP) in Boston and New York\, then co-founding the Treatment Act
 ion Group (TAG) and the International Treatment Preparedness Coalition (IT
 PC). He has also worked with Gay Men’s Health Crisis in New York and the
  AIDS and Rights Alliance for Southern Africa in Cape Town. He is a 2018 M
 acArthur Fellow.\n\nEvent URL: https://washington.zoom.us/meeting/register
 /hC13xdiQS4OKvW_Mh77qkA\n\nSource: uw_cfar
LOCATION:Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center\, Weintraub Building\, Pelton Audit
 orium\, 1100 Fairview Ave N\, Seattle\, WA 98109\, (Zoom option Available)
URL:https://washington.zoom.us/meeting/register/hC13xdiQS4OKvW_Mh77qkA
